---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Getting Started — Coherence by Viewyonder" description="Three steps to repo guardrails. Install the plugin, run /coherence, and you're enforcing architecture immediately.">
  <article class="container guide">
    <header class="guide-header">
      <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Home</a>
      <p class="section-label">Getting Started</p>
      <h1>Get Started</h1>
      <p class="guide-subtitle">
        Three steps to repo guardrails.
      </p>
    </header>

    <nav class="toc">
      <p class="toc-title">On this page</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#install">Install</a></li>
        <li><a href="#what-happens">What happens</a></li>
        <li><a href="#what-you-get">What you get</a></li>
        <li><a href="#project-types">Supported project types</a></li>
        <li><a href="#next-steps">Next steps</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="prose">

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="install" class="guide-section">
        <div class="path-badge path-badge-recommended">Recommended</div>
        <h2>Install</h2>
        <p>
          The Coherence plugin adds a single <code>/coherence</code> skill to Claude Code.
          It auto-detects your project state and generates a complete guardrails system —
          <code>CLAUDE.md</code>, SPEC docs, agents, and a nudge hook —
          customized to your stack.
        </p>

        <h3>1. Add the marketplace</h3>
        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-header">
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title">Claude Code</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /plugin marketplace add viewyonder/coherence
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>2. Install the plugin</h3>
        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-header">
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title">Claude Code</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /plugin install coherence
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <strong>Use user scope (the default).</strong>
          When Claude Code prompts you for a scope, choose <code>user</code> — or just press Enter to accept the default.
          Coherence is designed to work across all your projects: you install the plugin once, then run <code>/coherence</code> in each repo to generate project-specific guardrails.
          If you install with <code>local</code> scope, the plugin is locked to a single project and you'll get an "already installed" error when you try to install it elsewhere.
          See <a href="/plugins#installing">Plugin scopes</a> for details.
        </div>

        <h3>3. Run <code>/coherence</code></h3>
        <p>Open Claude Code in your project and run:</p>
        <div class="terminal">
          <div class="terminal-header">
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
            <span class="terminal-title">Claude Code</span>
          </div>
          <div class="terminal-body">
            <span class="prompt">&gt;</span> /coherence
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>4. Auto-detect in action</h3>
        <p>
          Coherence examines your project and picks the right mode automatically.
        </p>

        <div class="phase-list">
          <div class="phase">
            <div class="phase-num">1</div>
            <div class="phase-detail">
              <strong>Detect</strong>
              <span class="phase-auto">automatic</span>
              <p>Scans for existing SPEC files, CLAUDE.md references, language, framework, and project structure. Determines whether to scaffold, set up, or check drift.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="phase">
            <div class="phase-num">2</div>
            <div class="phase-detail">
              <strong>Confirm</strong>
              <span class="phase-questions">review</span>
              <p>Shows what it plans to do. Nothing is written until you confirm.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="phase">
            <div class="phase-num">3</div>
            <div class="phase-detail">
              <strong>Execute</strong>
              <span class="phase-auto">automatic</span>
              <p>Writes all files — CLAUDE.md, SPEC docs, agents, nudge hook, and settings — customized to your project.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="callout">
          <strong>Idempotent.</strong> If you already have a <code>.claude/</code> directory, Coherence asks whether to overwrite, merge, or abort. Use <code>/coherence scaffold</code> to force a fresh scaffold.
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="manual" class="guide-section">
        <details class="manual-details">
          <summary class="manual-summary">
            <h2>Alternative: Manual Template</h2>
            <p>Full control — copy the template and customize everything by hand.</p>
          </summary>

          <div class="manual-content">
            <h3>1. Copy the template</h3>
            <div class="terminal">
              <div class="terminal-header">
                <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
                <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
                <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
                <span class="terminal-title">bash</span>
              </div>
              <div class="terminal-body">
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cd /path/to/your/project<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Clone the repo (or download the template/ directory)</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> git clone https://github.com/viewyonder/coherence.git /tmp/ccg<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Copy the .claude directory</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cp -r /tmp/ccg/template/.claude .<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Copy CLAUDE.md template</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cp /tmp/ccg/template/CLAUDE.md .<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Copy SPEC + memory templates</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> mkdir -p docs<br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cp /tmp/ccg/template/docs/*.md docs/
              </div>
            </div>

            <h3>2. Customize CLAUDE.md</h3>
            <p>
              Replace every <code>{`{{PLACEHOLDER}}`}</code> marker with your project's values.
              The file has HTML comments explaining each one.
            </p>

            <h3>3. Configure hooks</h3>
            <p>
              Each hook has a <code>// === CONFIGURATION ===</code> block at the top.
              Edit the constants for your project's APIs, file paths, and boundaries.
              Remove hooks you don't need.
            </p>

            <h3>4. Update settings.local.json</h3>
            <p>
              Remove entries for any hooks you deleted. The file lives at
              <code>.claude/settings.local.json</code> — every hook referenced there must
              have a matching <code>.cjs</code> file.
            </p>

            <h3>5. Create your first SPEC</h3>
            <p>
              Copy a SPEC template from <code>docs/</code>, fill in your actual components,
              and run <code>/coherence</code> to verify.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="what-happens" class="guide-section">
        <h2>What Happens</h2>
        <p>
          After setup, your <code>.claude/</code> directory makes architectural constraints
          active during every development session.
        </p>

        <div class="flow-diagram">
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="flow-label">You (or Claude) edit files</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-arrow">&darr;</div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="flow-label">Nudge hook tracks edits</div>
            <div class="flow-detail">After 50 edits or 7 days, nudges you to check for drift</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-arrow">&darr;</div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="flow-label">Run <code>/coherence</code></div>
            <div class="flow-detail">Agents scan the full codebase against SPEC docs and principles</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-arrow">&darr;</div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <div class="flow-label">Fix any drift found</div>
            <div class="flow-detail">Or run <code>/coherence fix</code> to auto-apply corrections</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="what-you-get" class="guide-section">
        <h2>What You Get</h2>
        <p>
          Regardless of which path you choose, you end up with a <code>.claude/</code> directory
          that makes architectural constraints active during development.
        </p>

        <div class="file-tree">
          <div class="file-tree-header">your-project/</div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-0"><span class="file-icon">&#128196;</span> CLAUDE.md <span class="file-desc">— project guidelines, populated</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-0"><span class="file-icon">&#128193;</span> .claude/</div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1"><span class="file-icon">&#9881;</span> settings.local.json <span class="file-desc">— hook registration</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1"><span class="file-icon">&#128193;</span> hooks/</div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-2">spec-drift-nudge.cjs <span class="file-desc">— nudge after 50 edits or 7 days</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-2">_journal.cjs <span class="file-desc">— JSONL activity logging utility</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1"><span class="file-icon">&#128193;</span> agents/</div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-2">drift-detector.md <span class="file-desc">— compare SPEC vs code</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-2">spec-reviewer.md <span class="file-desc">— review plans against SPECs</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-2"><span class="file-muted">+ code-reviewer, consistency-reviewer, security-auditor</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1"><span class="file-icon">&#128193;</span> skills/</div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-2"><span class="file-icon">&#128193;</span> coherence/ <span class="file-desc">— single /coherence skill, auto-detecting</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-0"><span class="file-icon">&#128193;</span> docs/</div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1">SPEC-PRINCIPLES.md <span class="file-desc">— architectural principles</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1">SPEC-TEMPLATE.md <span class="file-desc">— template for project-specific SPECs</span></div>
          <div class="file-tree-item depth-1">SPEC-VERSIONING.md <span class="file-desc">— version locations and bump process</span></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="project-types" class="guide-section">
        <h2>Works with Any Project</h2>
        <p>
          <code>/coherence</code> auto-detects your language, framework, and project structure.
          It generates SPEC documents and CLAUDE.md content tailored to your stack —
          whether you're building a web app, API, CLI, infrastructure, or writing content.
          The same single hook and agents work across all project types.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- ============================================ -->
      <section id="next-steps" class="guide-section">
        <h2>Next Steps</h2>

        <div class="next-steps-list">
          <div class="next-step">
            <code>/coherence</code>
            <p>Run any time to check for drift. Coherence compares every SPEC claim against your codebase and reports what's current, drifted, or undocumented.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step">
            <code>/coherence plan</code>
            <p>Before implementing a plan, run this to review it against your SPEC constraints.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step">
            <code>/coherence fix</code>
            <p>Drift detection plus auto-apply — fixes issues it finds without manual intervention.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step">
            <code>/coherence version</code>
            <p>Bump your project version following SemVer. Updates all declared version locations, commits, and tags.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step">
            <span class="next-step-label">Edit CLAUDE.md</span>
            <p>The generated file is a starting point. Add your domain concepts, refine principles, document your actual architecture.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step">
            <a href="/plugins" class="next-step-label">Plugin reference</a>
            <p>Learn about plugin scopes, updates, local testing, and creating your own plugins.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="next-step">
            <span class="next-step-label">Read the blog post</span>
            <p><a href="/blog/entropy-at-velocity">Entropy at Velocity</a> explains the thinking behind this system.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .guide {
    padding-top: 7rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .guide-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .guide-subtitle {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    max-width: 50ch;
  }

  /* Table of contents */
  .toc {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .toc-title {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .toc ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .toc li {
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  .toc a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .toc a:hover {
    color: var(--cyan);
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .toc code {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .guide-section {
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .guide-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .guide-section h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .guide-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Path badges */
  .path-badge {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.2em 0.8em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .path-badge-recommended {
    background: rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.12);
    color: var(--green);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 136, 0.3);
  }

  /* Manual template (collapsed) */
  .manual-details {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .manual-summary {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .manual-summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .manual-summary::before {
    content: '\25B6';
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    display: inline-block;
    margin-right: 0.75rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s;
  }

  details[open] .manual-summary::before {
    transform: rotate(90deg);
  }

  .manual-summary h2 {
    display: inline;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .manual-summary p {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0 1.5rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .manual-content {
    padding: 0 1.5rem 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
  }

  /* Phase list */
  .phase-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .phase {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }

  .phase-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--cyan);
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.3);
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .phase-detail {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .phase-detail strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .phase-detail p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .phase-auto, .phase-questions {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    padding: 0.1em 0.5em;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
    vertical-align: middle;
  }

  .phase-auto {
    background: rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.1);
    color: var(--cyan);
  }

  .phase-questions {
    background: rgba(255, 170, 0, 0.12);
    color: var(--amber);
  }

  /* Callout */
  .callout {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--cyan);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .callout strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .callout-warn {
    border-left-color: var(--amber, #ffa600);
  }

  /* File tree */
  .file-tree {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    max-width: 550px;
  }

  .file-tree-header {
    color: var(--cyan);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
  }

  .file-tree-item {
    padding: 0.2rem 0;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .depth-0 { padding-left: 0; }
  .depth-1 { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  .depth-2 { padding-left: 3rem; }
  .depth-3 { padding-left: 4.5rem; }

  .file-icon {
    margin-right: 0.4rem;
  }

  .file-desc {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  .file-muted {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Flow diagram */
  .flow-diagram {
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    max-width: 450px;
  }

  .flow-step {
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .flow-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .flow-detail {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .flow-arrow {
    text-align: center;
    color: var(--cyan);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    padding: 0.25rem 0;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  /* Archetype grid */
  .archetype-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--gap);
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .archetype-card h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .archetype-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .archetype-hooks {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .archetype-hooks .badge {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
  }

  /* Next steps */
  .next-steps-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .next-step {
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--bg-mid);
    border: 1px solid var(--bg-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }

  .next-step code {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--cyan);
    background: rgba(0, 255, 240, 0.08);
  }

  .next-step-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  a.next-step-label {
    color: var(--cyan);
  }

  .next-step p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    margin-top: 0.35rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .phase {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .archetype-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
